<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The type material of 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. sbarbaronis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="sbarbaronis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. sbarbaronis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been located. 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuss, O" journalOrPublisher="Sauteria" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="121 - 138" refId="B6" refString="Breuss, O, 2008a. Bemerkungen zu einigen Arten der Flechtengattung Verrucaria. Sauteria 15: 121 - 138" title="Bemerkungen zu einigen Arten der Flechtengattung Verrucaria." volume="15" year="2008 a">Breuss (2008a)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. sbarbaronis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="sbarbaronis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. sbarbaronis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species rather similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. lacerata" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="lacerata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. lacerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which is here considered conspecific with 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subjunctiva" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subjunctiva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subjunctiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but with clearly smaller spores (20-26 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
11-15 mm). Such specimens have not been found from Finland.
